OL,3,CCinema shooter was fired from theatre
OL,4,Cfollowing staff complaints, court hears
OL,6,FHe approached cashier Danielle Mea and
OL,7,Fguard Philip Smith at the ticket desk,
OL,8,Fand pointed his AK47 at the two
OL,9,Fmembers of staff.JBoth workers
OL,10,F"believed it was a joke", with Mr
OL,11,FSmith even telling him: "Drop the
OL,12,Fpeashooter and don't point it at her."
OL,13,FBut Garrett responded "come see" and
OL,14,Fgestured for him to follow him into
OL,15,Fthe car park. Cameras then captured
OL,16,Fthe moment that he repeatedly fired
OL,17,Fthe gun outside the cinema.JUpon
OL,18,Frealising that the gun was live, Mr
OL,19,FSmith shouted to Ms Mea: "Get down.
OL,20,FGet out."JCustomers were "contained
OL,21,Ffor their safety whilst police secured
OL,22,Fthe area", with 12 shell casings being
OL,23,Frecovered from the scene.
